messages.content: What is the latest version of the ComfyUI Browser extension?
The latest version of the ComfyUI Browser extension is v1.8.1, released on 2024-03-22.
What feature was added in version 1.8.1 of the ComfyUI Browser extension?
In version 1.8.1 of the ComfyUI Browser extension, the xyz_plot node was updated to support the score mode.
When was the Z-axis support for xyz_plot added to the ComfyUI Browser extension?
The Z-axis support for xyz_plot was added to the ComfyUI Browser extension in version 1.8.0, released on 2024-03-19.
What new nodes were added in version 1.7.0 of the ComfyUI Browser extension?
In version 1.7.0 of the ComfyUI Browser extension, released on 2024-01-14, the xyz_plot and select_inputs nodes were added.
When was i18n support and the zh-CN language added to the ComfyUI Browser extension?
i18n support and the zh-CN language were added to the ComfyUI Browser extension in version 1.6.0, released on 2023-12-30.
Which version of the ComfyUI Browser extension introduced the 'Sources' tab for subscribing to external workflow git repositories?
The 'Sources' tab for subscribing to external workflow git repositories was introduced in version 1.4.0 of the ComfyUI Browser extension, released on 2023-12-13.
When was the ability to collect the current graph to Collections as a workflow.json added to the ComfyUI Browser extension?
The ability to collect the current graph to Collections as a workflow.json was added to the ComfyUI Browser extension in version 1.2.0, released on 2023-12-10.
What is create-svelte used for?
create-svelte is used to create and set up a new Svelte project with the necessary dependencies and configuration.
How do you create a new Svelte project?
You can create a new Svelte project by running the command 'npm create svelte@latest' in the current directory or 'npm create svelte@latest my-app' to create a new project in a specific directory.
What should be done after creating a new Svelte project?
After creating a new Svelte project, you should install the dependencies using 'npm install', 'pnpm install', or 'yarn'.
How can you start the development server for a Svelte project?
You can start the development server for a Svelte project by running the command 'npm run dev' or 'npm run dev -- --open' to also open the app in a new browser tab.
How do you create a production build of a Svelte app?
To create a production build of a Svelte app, you should run 'npm run build'. You can then preview the production build using 'npm run preview'.
What may be required to deploy a Svelte app?
To deploy a Svelte app, you may need to install an adapter suitable for your target environment.
Where can you find more information about Svelte adapters?
You can find more information about Svelte adapters in the official documentation at https://kit.svelte.dev/docs/adapters.
What is the main purpose of the ComfyUI browser?
The main purpose of the ComfyUI browser is to view and manage all output files of ComfyUI, and to add favorites for easy invocation at any time.
How can you synchronize workflows remotely using the ComfyUI browser?
You can synchronize workflows remotely using the ComfyUI browser through Git to your Git repository, which is convenient for team sharing and version management.
What is one of the ways to install the ComfyUI browser?
One of the ways to install the ComfyUI browser is by installing ComfyUI Manager, then searching for 'comfyui-browser' in Install Custom Node to install it.
How can you subscribe to workflow repositories using the ComfyUI browser?
You can subscribe to workflow repositories using the ComfyUI browser, which makes it convenient to copy workflows.
What framework is used for the backend of the ComfyUI browser?
The backend of the ComfyUI browser uses the aiohttp framework.
How can you open or close the ComfyUI browser within ComfyUI?
You can press the 'B' key within ComfyUI to open or close the ComfyUI browser.
Where can you find the update history of the ComfyUI browser?
The update history of the ComfyUI browser can be found in the ChangeLog.
What is the name of the workflow repository?
The name of the workflow repository is 'New workflow repository'.
What is the title of the workflow repository?
The title of the workflow repository is 'New workflow repo:'.
What labels are assigned to the workflow repository?
The label assigned to the workflow repository is 'workflow-repo'.
Who is the assignee for the workflow repository?
The assignee for the workflow repository is 'tzwm'.
Is there a link provided for the workflow repository?
Yes, there is a mention of a workflow repository link in the text.
Is there a description for the workflow repository?
Yes, there is a 'Description' section mentioned in the text for the workflow repository.
What is the purpose of the workflow repository based on the title?
Based on the title 'New workflow repo:', the purpose of the workflow repository is to introduce a new workflow repository.
